No fewer than five people were shot dead by suspected cultists in Ilesha, Osun State. The Nation learnt that the cultists unleashed mayhem in several parts of the community.   Many injured in Ilorin hoodlums’ brawl     Police arrest three men for gang-rape      Gunmen kill two policemen in Anambra   A resident of the community, who pleaded anonymity, said the clash took place around 7 pm on Monday. “The cultists were shooting intermittently and without any hindrance. They even shot at residents who they perceived to be a threat to their activities.” Police spokesperson Yemisi Opalola confirmed the incident, saying, “Operatives have been deployed to the areas”.